\p 
\v 22 For also many times your heart knows that even you have belittled others.
\p 
\v 23 All of this I tested with wisdom. I said, “Let me be wise,” but it {was} far from me.
\p 
\v 24 Far away is that which was, and deep, deep. Who will find it?
\p 
\v 25 I turned, I and my heart, to know and to explore, {to} seek wisdom and the scheme of things, and to know {the} wickedness {that is} folly and the foolishness {that is} madness.
\p 
\v 26 And I found more bitter than death {is} the woman who, snares she {is}, and her heart, nets; her hands, chains. The one who is good to the face of God will flee from her, but a sinner will be captured by her.
\p 
